 Port Elizabeth - A 26-year-old man from Bethelsddorp, in Port Elizabeth, is expected in court on Monday after he was arrested by police for the illegal possession of a firearm. "Continuous seizures and confiscation of illegal and stolen firearms is a step closer to reducing serious and violent crimes as well as firearm related crimes," said police spokesperson, Col Priscilla Naidu. "On Friday, at about 21:05, SAPS Bethelsdorp members were patrolling in a hotspot area in Booysens Park when they noticed a suspicious male in Prince Street. "The members stopped and on searching him, found a firearm under his armpit." Col Naidu said that the the suspect resisted but was overpowered by police. "The firearm, a 9mm pistol was reported stolen in Nooigedacht Road in Booyens Park, Port Elizabeth, in October 2019," she added. "The 26-year-old suspect is detained on a charge of illegal possession of a firearm and ammunition." He will appear in the Port Elizabeth magistrates’ court on Monday. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 